en_862496_0	The Bribery or Corruption Allegations Investigation Commission has decided to formulate National Action Plan to eliminate bribery and corruption from the country.
en_862496_1	A workshop was held in Colombo to garner the views of journalists and representatives of the civil society organizations in this regard.
en_862496_2	The workshop was organized by the Bribery or Corruption Investigations Commission.
en_862496_3	Several leading intellectuals opined their views in the workshop.
en_862496_4	Addressing the gathering Director General of the Commission,SarathJayamannarequested the youth to join hands with the new endeavor to uproot bribery and corruption in the country.
en_862496_5	He requested not to limit to social media spheres in this regard.
en_862496_6	The Director General pointed out that even foreigners who love Sri Lanka have divulged information pertaining to mega scale frauds.
en_862496_7	He also urged the business community to refrain from giving bribes and report such incidents with immediate effect.
en_862496_8	He highlighted that it is not just a duty of the watchdogs in bribery and corruption but also of the general public and other stakeholders.
en_862496_9	Additional Secretary of the Ministry of Finance and Mass Media, Chairperson of the ITN Media Network, ThilakaJayasundera said that commitment of the people towards ending bribery and corruption is a huge service rendered on behalf of the motherland.
en_862496_10	She requested the journalists in the country to extend their support to make the national action plan a success.
en_862496_11	The Media content generated by the journalists is highly influential and profound in eliminating corruption.
en_862496_12	She requested to use their practice in journalism for the betterment of the country.
en_862496_13	Commissioner of the Bribery or Corruption Allegations Commission, Neville Guruge said that only 25 percent of the government employees are linked with some corrupt activities.
en_862496_14	75 percent of the employees of the government sector continue a clean career that has not been marred by corruption.
